# Doc / PR / code parity

## Why this rule exists

- PR #37 (Copilot): PR description named the helper
  `enqueueResearchRetryJob` but only `enqueueResearchRetryJobWithCleanup`
  was exported.
- PR #40 (Copilot): `runStateMachine.ts` header doc referenced
  `decideRunStateOnSuccess` / `decideRunStateOnCancel` and a frontend
  file `frontend/src/utils/runState.ts`, none of which exist.
- PR #40 (user, after merge attempt): the V2 ensemble PR claimed
  "OpenRouter, multi-provider redundant" but verification on
  `openrouter.ai/api/v1/models/<slug>/endpoints` showed most slugs were
  single-upstream on OpenRouter.

## Rule — PR body / doc parity

Before pushing the final commit on a branch:

1. **Re-read the PR body / README change / doc against the final commit
   diff.** Every named symbol must exist; every referenced file must
   exist; every linked path must resolve. Use `Grep` if needed.
2. **Drop aspirational language.** If a function might be added later
   but is not in this PR, do not describe it as if it exists. Use
   "future work" / "follow-up".
3. **Names in the PR body must match the final exported names.**

## Rule — external-system claims

Any claim about an external system in a doc, PR body, or header
comment must be verified against the external system itself, not
recalled from memory:

| Claim shape | Required verification |
|---|---|
| "Available on HF Inference Providers" | `hub_repo_details` or model card `availableInferenceProviders` |
| "Multi-provider on OpenRouter" | `GET https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/models/<slug>/endpoints` and count entries |
| "Costs $X per 1M tokens" | Live model catalog at the provider |
| "Multi-region uptime" | The provider's status page |
| "Slug exists" | The catalog list itself |
| "Behavior X under load" | An actual test or a benchmark |

If the verification cannot be performed (no internet access in this
run, no time, etc.), **say so explicitly in the doc** — write
"unverified, requires deploy-side check" rather than asserting the
claim.

## Concrete examples in this repo

- ✅ `docs/V2_MODEL_SELECTION_CRITERIA.md` now includes the verified
  per-slug provider count (Nebius / DeepInfra / Venice / NextBit) and
  explicitly notes the "multi-provider redundant" framing was overstated.
- ✅ `runStateMachine.ts` header doc lists only the exports that
  actually exist: `decideRunStateOnFailure`,
  `decideRunStateOnRetryRequest`, `rejectionToHttpBody`.

## Pre-commit check

Before `git push` on the final commit of a branch:
- [ ] Did you `Grep` the final diff for every symbol named in the PR body?
- [ ] Did you re-read the PR body end-to-end against the final commit?
- [ ] If the body / doc claims something about an external system, did
  you verify it live in this session?
